# Modiba Stability Rules

- Never break working behavior; prefer minimal, safe changes.
- Analyze root cause first, then modify code.
- Do not change auth/signing, external API request shape, env/secrets, infra/deploy config, DB schema, or core business logic without explicit user approval.
- Must ask before multi-file changes, dependency additions, API contract changes, file delete/rename, or infra-impacting edits.
- Safe auto-run scope: UI improvements, logging/debug, and small single-file bug fixes.
- Error triage defaults:
  - 403: check IP/auth first
  - 400: check request format first
  - 500: check server-side/runtime first
- Security: never expose API keys; never log sensitive data.
- Prioritize stability over speed in every change.
